      {
        "user": "How does \"Token Tax\" differ from token cost / API cost-per-token?",
        "assistant": "“Token tax” and “API cost-per-token” are unrelated concepts that both use the word **token** differently.\n\n### 1. Token tax: crypto fee\n\nA **token tax** is usually a fee built into a cryptocurrency token’s smart contract.\n\nExample:\n\n- You sell $1,000 of a crypto token.\n- The token has a 5% sell tax.\n- $50 is taken by the token contract.\n- You receive $950 before other fees.\n\nThis applies to blockchain tokens such as ERC-20, BEP-20, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 2. API cost-per-token: AI usage pricing\n\nIn AI APIs, a **token** is a chunk of text processed by the model. It can be a word, part of a word, punctuation, or formatting.\n\nExample:\n\n> “Hello world”\n\nmight be 2 tokens, while a longer paragraph may be hundreds of tokens.\n\n**API cost-per-token** means you pay based on how many text tokens are sent to and generated by the model.\n\nUsually there are two categories:\n\n- **Input tokens:** text you send to the model\n- **Output tokens:** text the model generates back\n\nExample:\n\n- You send 1,000 input tokens.\n- The model returns 500 output tokens.\n- You are billed based on those token counts and the model’s pricing.\n\n---\n\n### Key difference\n\n| Concept | Meaning of “token” | What you pay for | Where it applies |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Token tax** | Crypto asset/token | A transaction fee on buying, selling, or transferring | Blockchain / DeFi |\n| **API cost-per-token** | Unit of text | Model processing and generation | AI APIs / LLMs |\n\nSo, **token tax is a crypto transaction fee**, while **API cost-per-token is usage-based pricing for text processed by an AI model**.",
